{0 Go to definition}

Jump from a link to its definition target within an Oystermark vault.

{1 Input}

A cursor position (0-based line and character) in a markdown file that
belongs to a vault with a built index.

{1:link_detection Link detection}

The cursor must fall within the byte range of a recognized link form:

{ul
  {- {b Wikilinks}: [[[target]]], [[[target#heading]]],
     [[[target#^blockid]]], [![[embed]]]}
  {- {b Markdown links}: [[text](target)]}
  {- {b Markdown images}: [![alt](img.png)]}
}

External URLs ([https://...], [http://...]) are {e not} recognized as
navigable links and produce no result.

{1:resolution Resolution}

Once a link is detected, it is resolved against the vault index via
{!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve}.  The resolution cases and their
results are:

{t
  | Link form                 | Target path       | Target position               |
  |---------------------------|-------------------|-------------------------------|
  | [[[note]]]                | resolved file     | top of file (line 0, char 0)  |
  | [[text](note)]            | resolved file     | line 0, char 0                |
  | [![[file.png]]]           | resolved file     | line 0, char 0                |
  | [[[note#Heading]]]        | resolved file     | position of matching heading  |
  | [[[note#^blockid]]]       | resolved file     | position of matching block    |
  | [[[note#id]]]             | resolved file     | position of attribute anchor  |
  | [[[#Heading]]]            | current file      | position of heading           |
  | [[[#^blockid]]]           | current file      | position of block             |
  | [[[#id]]]                 | current file      | position of attribute anchor  |
  | unresolved link           | {e None}          | —                             |
}

{2 Heading lookup}

Headings are matched by {e slug}: the heading text is slugified (e.g.
"Section One" becomes [section-one]) and compared against the fragment.
The position is read from the heading AST node's [Cmarkit.Textloc]
metadata.

{2 Block-ID lookup}

Block IDs ([^id] suffix on a paragraph) are matched by exact string
comparison on the ID.  The position is read from the paragraph AST
node's [Cmarkit.Textloc] metadata.

{2 Attribute-anchor lookup}

A fragment naming an explicit djot attribute id ([{#id}]) resolves to the
attributed inline span, block, or heading. See
{!page-"feature-attribute-anchors"} for how ids are collected and how the
fragment namespace (slug, caret id, attribute id) is searched. The
position is read from the attributed node's [Cmarkit.Textloc]; for an
{e inline} anchor this is column-precise, so the jump lands mid-line.

{2:target_position Target position (line and character)}

Both the 0-based [line] and the 0-based [character] of the target are
derived from the resolved node's [Cmarkit.Textloc]:

{ul
  {- [line] is [fst (first_line loc) - 1] (the [Textloc] line number is
     one-based).}
  {- [character] is a UTF-16 code-unit offset within the line (see
     {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}). It is computed by decoding the
     line's bytes from [snd (first_line loc)] to [first_byte loc] via
     {!Lsp_lib.Util.position_of_textloc}, using the {e target file's}
     content.}
}

The target content is obtained from the current buffer for self-file
targets ([Curr_heading]/[Curr_block]/[Curr_attr]) and via the [read_file]
callback for cross-file targets ([Heading]/[Block]/[Attr]). The raw file
content is used directly: [Textloc] offsets are aligned with the original
file, including files with YAML frontmatter, because the parser blanks
(rather than strips) the frontmatter region — see
{!Oystermark.Parse.Frontmatter.blank_frontmatter}. If [read_file] returns
[None], [character] degrades to a byte offset.

Targets without a location (whole-file [Note]/[File], self-reference
[Curr_file]) resolve to line 0, character 0.

{2 Fallback}

If the target heading, block ID, or attribute id is not found in the
target file, the result falls back to line 0, character 0.

{1:edge_cases Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Cursor outside any link}: no result.}
  {- {b Character offset past end of line}: clamped to content length.}
  {- {b Line past end of content}: clamped to end of content.}
}

{1 Multi-target ambiguity}

When {!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve} returns multiple candidates,
go-to-definition picks the first candidate (per vault resolution order).

{1 Embed links}

Embed links ([![[note]]]) are treated identically to regular wikilinks
for navigation: the target is the embedded file at line 0.  No distinct
behavior (e.g. inline preview) is provided by this feature.

{1 Assumptions and limitations}

{ul
  {- Position encoding: see {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}.}
  {- The document is re-parsed on every request (no caching).}
}
